{
  "texts": [
    "Following such criteria, a team of professional and independent journalists assigns a \"trust score\" between 0 and 100 to each news outlet.",
    "Ratings are not provided for individuals, satirical content, or social media platforms like Twitter, Facebook, and YouTube.",
    "News sources are categorized into two groups based on their score: Reliable (trust score greater or equal to 60) and Questionable (trust score less than 60).",
    "The threshold is set by NewsGuard",
    "Breakdown of the NewsGuard news sources dataset by country and reliability."
  ]
}